{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Don't be troubled bout me cause I'm tired
[G7]From working round the house when day is done
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Don't think you failed me cause you can't afford
[C]That dishwasher to make my life more fun
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C7]You know the measure of a man is much more
[F]Than just the money he can make
[C]And every woman knows a lot of joy
[G7]And tears come with the wedding [C]cake
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
The wedding cake is not all icing
[G7]And loving tender whispers in the dark
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
One slice is concern for all your dreams
[C]Afraid they won't come true and break your heart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Another slice is feeding kids and wiping noses
[F]Crying when the doorbell rings and there are [Fm]roses
[C]Every woman knows a lot of give
[G7]And take comes with the wedding [C]cake
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
It's facing shadows of the future prayin' they will fall away
[G7]As we walk towards them searching for the sun
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
And it's long and anxious hours with the wolf at the door
[C]Hugs and kisses when at last we see the dawn
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
So when the hands of time trace tiny lines
[F]Upon our face and lace our hair with strands [Fm]of gray
[C]We'll laugh and say for all who will partake
[G7]It all comes with the wedding [C]cake
{end_of_verse}








